name: Blastoise
flavorText: A brutal Pokemon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokemon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Extra Water Energy after the 2nd doesn't count.

name: Charizard
flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard in order to use this attack.

name: Venusaur
flavorText: This plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Grass Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokemon and attach it to a different one. This power can't be used if Venusaur is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Rocket's Zapdos
Attack1Text: If there are any Lightning Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Rocket's Zapdos.
Attack2Text: Rocket's Zapdos does damage to itself equal to 10 times the number of Lightning Energy cards attached to it.

name: Claydol
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose up to 2 cards from your hand and put them on the bottom of your deck in any order. If you do, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Claydol is affected by a Special Condition.

name: Dark Gyarados
flavorText: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.
Ability1Text: When Dark Gyarados is Knocked Out by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this power does 20 damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Gyarados to the Pokemon that Knocked Out Dark Gyarados. Apply Weakness and Resistance. This power doesn't work if Dark Gyarados is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: _____'s Pikachu
Attack1Text: If it's not your birthday, this attack does 30 damage. If it is your birthday, flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 50 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage.

name: Cleffa
flavorText: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 7 cards.

name: Shining Magikarp
flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions, but never more than seven feet.
Attack1Text: Your opponent may draw 2 cards. Either way, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for a card named Gyarados, Dark Gyarados, or Shining Gyarados. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Team Magma's Groudon
Ability1Text: As long as the number of Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) that has Team Magma in its name is 3 or less, Team Magma's Groudon can't attack.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon already has at least 2 damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Mew ex
Ability1Text: Mew ex can use the attacks of all Pokemon in play as its own. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to Mew ex. Shuffle your deck afterward. Then, you may switch Mew ex with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Gardevoir ex δ
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Gardevoir ex is your Active Pokemon, you may put an Imprison marker on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Any Pokemon that has any Imprison markers on it can't use any Poke-Powers or Poke-Bodies. This power can't be used if Gardevoir ex is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: You may move a Fire Energy card attached to Gardevoir ex to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Umbreon ★
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Umbreon Star from your hand onto your Bench, you may choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.

name: Luxray GL LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Luxray GL LV.X from your hand onto your Active Luxray GL, you may switch the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your Pokemon, and don't apply Weakness and Resistance to this damage.

name: Garchomp C LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Garchomp C LV.X from your hand onto your Active Garchomp C, you may remove all damage counters from each of your Pokemon SP.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Garchomp C. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 80 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Garchomp C can't use Dragon Rush during your next turn.

name: Donphan
Ability1Text: Any damage done to Donphan by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Reshiram
flavorText: This Pokemon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Zekrom
flavorText: This Pokemon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 40 damage to itself.

name: Mewtwo-EX
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Xerneas-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use X Blast during your next turn.

name: M Rayquaza-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the number of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Tapu Lele-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to both Active Pokemon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack2Text: Heal all damage from 2 of your Benched Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
